<HEADLINE>
TAIWAN TO DONATE WHEELCHAIRS TO DIPLOMATIC ALLIES
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei,   March  16  (CNA) 03/16/07  19:56:27 (By Luis Huang)
</P>
<P>
A volunteer activity to assemble wheelchairs will be held
Saturday at the Taoyuan branch of Chang Gung Memorial Hospital
and the wheelchairs will be donated to Taiwan's diplomatic allies
to highlight the nation's spirit of humanitarian aid, a Ministry
of Foreign Affairs (MOFA) official said Friday.
</P>
<P>
According to the official, the activity is being organized by the
MOFA's NGO Affairs Commission, the Eden Social Welfare
Foundation, the Pu Hsein Foundation and the Chang Gung Memorial
Hospital.
</P>
<P>
The official said that ambassadors of Taiwan's diplomatic allies
stationed in Taipei and foreign students pursuing advanced
studies here under a scholarship program sponsored by the
Democratic Pacific Union have been also invited to take part in
the event.
</P>
<P>
During the activity, Minister of Foreign Affairs James Huang and
his wife, as well as other MOFA officials and members of their
families will help assemble the 30 wheelchairs, the official
said, adding that Huang will deliver the 30 wheelchairs to the
foreign envoys of the recipient countries.
</P>
<P>
The official further said the Eden Social Welfare Foundation and
the Pu Hsein Foundation have cooperated with the Foreign Ministry
every year since 1996 and 1998, respectively, in donating
wheelchairs to friendly nations in Southeast Asia, the Middle
East and Africa in an effort to build a good image for the
country.
</P>
